.TH btctax-reconcile-classify-inbound-self-transfer 1  btctax "btctax manual"
.SH NAME
classify\-inbound\-self\-transfer \- Classify an inbound TransferIn as an inbound self\-transfer ("my own coins" returning) — non\-taxable, creates a fresh lot. `\-\-basis` defaults to $0 (conservative; fires the honest zero\-basis advisory when omitted); `\-\-acquired` defaults to the receipt date (short\-term)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBclassify\-inbound\-self\-transfer\fR [\fB\-\-basis\fR] [\fB\-\-acquired\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIIN_REF\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Classify an inbound TransferIn as an inbound self\-transfer ("my own coins" returning) — non\-taxable, creates a fresh lot. `\-\-basis` defaults to $0 (conservative; fires the honest zero\-basis advisory when omitted); `\-\-acquired` defaults to the receipt date (short\-term)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-basis\fR \fI<BASIS>\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-acquired\fR \fI<ACQUIRED>\fR

.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIIN_REF\fR>

